1
00:00:59,860 --> 00:01:00,960
<b>I beg of you, ma'am.</b>

2
00:01:02,300 --> 00:01:03,870
<b>Please reconsider it.</b>

3
00:01:04,100 --> 00:01:06,070
<b>If the reason you're trying to hold...</b>

4
00:01:07,030 --> 00:01:09,600
<b>the committee is because it's your son...</b>

5
00:01:10,370 --> 00:01:12,810
<b>Please take it out on me.</b>

6
00:01:13,980 --> 00:01:17,580
<b>It's my fault for raising him poorly.</b>

7
00:01:18,150 --> 00:01:19,580
<b>You can take it out on me...</b>

8
00:01:20,410 --> 00:01:21,720
<b>however you like.</b>

9
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:23,850
<b>Then let's see what you can do...</b>

10
00:01:24,550 --> 00:01:26,220
<b>to relieve my anger.</b>

11
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:31,660
<b>Please, ma'am.</b>

12
00:01:33,090 --> 00:01:34,130
<b>Forgive him...</b>

13
00:01:35,460 --> 00:01:36,630
<b>just this once.</b>

14
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,070
<b>Please get up.</b>

15
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:45,640
<b>What do you think you're doing?</b>

16
00:01:46,070 --> 00:01:48,010
<b>Get up, Yoon Ji Su!</b>

17
00:02:11,330 --> 00:02:13,830
<b>Explain what's going on.</b>

18
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:17,100
<b>What's going on?</b>

19
00:02:17,410 --> 00:02:19,440
<b>- Ms. Jang. - Take Ms. Yoon...</b>

20
00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:20,780
<b>and excuse us.</b>

21
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:22,310
<b>Sure.</b>

22
00:02:37,660 --> 00:02:39,690
<b>I told you not to make this an issue.</b>

23
00:02:39,890 --> 00:02:42,000
<b>You talked about a young boy's future...</b>

24
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:44,300
<b>and acted as if you were so righteous.</b>

25
00:02:45,270 --> 00:02:46,500
<b>Was it about a woman?</b>

26
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:49,040
<b>Why did you call her name...</b>

27
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:50,300
<b>and act so besotted?</b>

28
00:02:50,570 --> 00:02:51,710
<b>She's a university friend.</b>

29
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:54,910
<b>Your first love?</b>

30
00:02:55,510 --> 00:02:57,410
<b>Like the film "Love Letter"?</b>

31
00:02:59,510 --> 00:03:03,450
<b>I didn't want to turn the kids' problem into ours,</b>

32
00:03:03,650 --> 00:03:05,350
<b>but you just won't listen.</b>

33
00:03:05,750 --> 00:03:06,850
<b>What do you mean?</b>

34
00:03:07,390 --> 00:03:08,920
<b>If you don't cancel the committee,</b>

35
00:03:09,490 --> 00:03:10,660
<b>that Se Hwi.</b>

36
00:03:12,730 --> 00:03:15,660
<b>The guy called Se Hwi will never get to model again.</b>

37
00:03:15,830 --> 00:03:18,670
<b>He has nothing to do with this.</b>

38
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:20,270
<b>He has something to do with you.</b>

39
00:03:20,530 --> 00:03:24,010
<b>You'll ruin someone's bright future over something like this?</b>

40
00:03:24,010 --> 00:03:25,270
<b>I'd like to say...</b>

41
00:03:26,340 --> 00:03:28,710
<b>the exact same thing to your face.</b>

42
00:03:33,910 --> 00:03:36,250
<b>Do you know how much they donated to us?</b>

43
00:03:37,220 --> 00:03:39,250
<b>If Jun Seo transfers to another school,</b>

44
00:03:39,420 --> 00:03:42,520
<b>we'll have to stop working on the new gymnasium.</b>

45
00:03:43,260 --> 00:03:45,490
<b>And we'll have to fire 4 or 5 teachers too.</b>

46
00:03:46,230 --> 00:03:48,560
<b>- Did it have to be Jun Seo... - I apologize.</b>

47
00:03:49,060 --> 00:03:50,530
<b>But I feel that...</b>

48
00:03:52,130 --> 00:03:54,470
<b>my Young Min must've felt lonely.</b>

49
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:58,010
<b>This school's in the middle of nowhere,</b>

50
00:03:58,270 --> 00:04:01,110
<b>so everyone feels lonely and wants to go home.</b>

51
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:03,080
<b>Do all lonely kids resort to violence?</b>

52
00:04:12,690 --> 00:04:13,850
<b>What about your wife?</b>

53
00:04:14,420 --> 00:04:17,020
<b>The School Violence Committee will not meet.</b>

54
00:04:18,060 --> 00:04:19,460
<b>Did your wife agree...</b>

55
00:04:19,460 --> 00:04:22,530
<b>If you go against me again, my son will change schools.</b>

56
00:05:22,990 --> 00:05:24,790
<b>I'll drop you off on the way.</b>

57
00:05:25,230 --> 00:05:26,290
<b>No, thanks.</b>

58
00:05:27,230 --> 00:05:29,230
<b>We gave you a tough time.</b>

59
00:05:30,930 --> 00:05:31,930
<b>You did.</b>

60
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:33,900
<b>It hurts.</b>

61
00:05:35,170 --> 00:05:38,410
<b>My wrist hurts, and so do my knees.</b>

62
00:05:39,140 --> 00:05:42,310
<b>Get in. A car ride is better when your joints hurt.</b>

63
00:05:42,340 --> 00:05:44,980
<b>No, it's not my joints that hurt.</b>

64
00:05:47,050 --> 00:05:49,180
<b>I'm not that frail yet.</b>

65
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:50,720
<b>I know.</b>

66
00:06:58,620 --> 00:06:59,850
<b>My gosh.</b>

67
00:07:27,350 --> 00:07:30,620
<b>Drop me off at the station. I can manage from there.</b>

68
00:07:30,850 --> 00:07:32,320
<b>I'll drop you off at Seoul Station.</b>

69
00:07:33,190 --> 00:07:35,360
<b>No. At the train station here.</b>

70
00:07:35,420 --> 00:07:37,490
<b>You can't buy shoes here.</b>

71
00:07:37,490 --> 00:07:38,630
<b>I can walk.</b>

72
00:07:40,190 --> 00:07:42,430
<b>I wouldn't care if I hadn't seen,</b>

73
00:07:42,430 --> 00:07:44,930
<b>but I did and I can't let you walk in that state.</b>

74
00:07:45,470 --> 00:07:47,370
<b>You're not a starving kid.</b>

75
00:07:47,370 --> 00:07:50,440
<b>What grown-up wears boots with a broken heel?</b>

76
00:07:52,340 --> 00:07:53,610
<b>Are you okay?</b>

77
00:07:54,410 --> 00:07:56,840
<b>- About what? - Your wife.</b>

78
00:07:58,710 --> 00:08:00,010
<b>Are you okay?</b>

79
00:08:01,020 --> 00:08:02,880
<b>You bowed deeply twice,</b>

80
00:08:03,150 --> 00:08:05,020
<b>and today you even went on your knees.</b>

81
00:08:05,620 --> 00:08:08,720
<b>I can do that a hundred or a thousand times.</b>

82
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:12,560
<b>If only to stop my son from crying.</b>

83
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:17,530
<b>To me, that is love.</b>

84
00:08:18,530 --> 00:08:19,800
<b>Not making someone cry.</b>

85
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,640
<b>So I understand your wife too.</b>

86
00:08:24,770 --> 00:08:27,010
<b>We protect our love in different ways.</b>

87
00:08:28,210 --> 00:08:31,410
<b>I'll say this just in case.</b>

88
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:34,250
<b>I didn't cancel the committee just for you.</b>

89
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:37,790
<b>He still denies it,</b>

90
00:08:39,020 --> 00:08:41,390
<b>but I think my son bullied yours.</b>

91
00:08:43,390 --> 00:08:45,730
<b>In elementary school, he was a ringleader...</b>

92
00:08:45,730 --> 00:08:47,730
<b>and got into trouble for bullying other kids.</b>

93
00:08:48,530 --> 00:08:50,000
<b>His mom's indifferent,</b>

94
00:08:50,970 --> 00:08:53,000
<b>and his grandfather's always on his side,</b>

95
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:55,700
<b>so he didn't fear anything.</b>

96
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:58,110
<b>I'm ashamed to say this,</b>

97
00:08:58,110 --> 00:09:00,170
<b>but I'll talk to Jun Seo.</b>

98
00:09:00,170 --> 00:09:02,580
<b>You should talk to Young Min.</b>

99
00:09:11,890 --> 00:09:17,460
<b>(When My Love Blooms)</b>

100
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:23,760
<b>I'll take you home. Your boots...</b>

101
00:09:24,160 --> 00:09:25,770
<b>It's a minute if I run.</b>

102
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:34,980
<b>I might have shoes in the trunk. Wait.</b>

103
00:09:35,140 --> 00:09:36,410
<b>It's really okay.</b>

104
00:09:44,350 --> 00:09:45,520
<b>I'll take these.</b>

105
00:09:54,530 --> 00:09:56,860
<b>These are for men, so they'll be big.</b>

106
00:09:57,060 --> 00:09:58,670
<b>Still, they'll be better than that.</b>

107
00:09:59,130 --> 00:10:01,700
<b>It's really okay. It's a hassle to return them.</b>

108
00:10:01,700 --> 00:10:02,900
<b>You don't have to return them.</b>

109
00:10:02,970 --> 00:10:05,540
<b>Wear them when you take out the trash.</b>

110
00:10:06,340 --> 00:10:08,740
<b>They weren't at all expensive, so no pressure.</b>

111
00:10:09,310 --> 00:10:10,580
<b>- Okay? - The pressure...</b>

112
00:11:02,230 --> 00:11:05,670
<b>(December 1993)</b>

113
00:11:17,410 --> 00:11:20,050
<b>Are you a huge rock star? Why are you the last to show?</b>

114
00:11:20,050 --> 00:11:22,080
<b>My dad wouldn't let me come.</b>

115
00:11:22,220 --> 00:11:24,690
<b>I had to sneak out.</b>

116
00:11:24,950 --> 00:11:27,490
<b>You always trip up and you still want to protest?</b>

117
00:11:31,690 --> 00:11:33,090
<b>Don't lose me.</b>

118
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:35,000
<b>Don't look anywhere else.</b>

119
00:11:35,130 --> 00:11:36,260
<b>Follow my footsteps.</b>

120
00:12:17,540 --> 00:12:18,910
<b>Are you all right?</b>

121
00:12:22,580 --> 00:12:23,780
<b>What do you want?</b>

122
00:12:24,810 --> 00:12:27,150
<b>Wow. Your face looks like it'll explode.</b>

123
00:12:32,220 --> 00:12:34,890
<b>Everyone thinks you can drink a lot.</b>

124
00:12:35,420 --> 00:12:37,420
<b>You can dupe others but not me.</b>

125
00:12:38,330 --> 00:12:39,990
<b>I'm always looking at you.</b>

126
00:12:42,060 --> 00:12:43,100
<b>Are you...</b>

127
00:12:46,700 --> 00:12:47,700
<b>like "Misery"?</b>

128
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:50,070
<b>How did you know?</b>

129
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:51,570
<b>My gosh.</b>

130
00:12:53,140 --> 00:12:55,040
<b>I thought you were like "Love Letter".</b>

131
00:12:57,440 --> 00:12:58,810
<b>You're "Misery".</b>

132
00:13:01,010 --> 00:13:02,750
<b>That's what people think,</b>

133
00:13:02,820 --> 00:13:06,050
<b>but I'm more like the horror, thriller, psycho genre.</b>

134
00:13:07,550 --> 00:13:10,160
<b>That doesn't mean I don't like "Love Letter".</b>

135
00:13:11,060 --> 00:13:12,690
<b>It's such a nice story.</b>

136
00:13:12,990 --> 00:13:15,760
<b>And the final scene is so moving.</b>

137
00:13:16,730 --> 00:13:18,970
<b>The snow field scene is so sad.</b>

138
00:13:31,750 --> 00:13:32,810
<b>You have...</b>

139
00:13:33,750 --> 00:13:35,120
<b>beautiful eyebrows.</b>

140
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:52,960
<b>Sleep well, Han Jae Hyun.</b>

141
00:15:07,710 --> 00:15:08,980
<b>I'm freezing.</b>

142
00:15:23,590 --> 00:15:30,030
<b>(Jae Hyun, Ji Su)</b>

143
00:15:51,790 --> 00:15:54,690
<b>Let's hear your love story.</b>

144
00:15:58,360 --> 00:16:00,330
<b>I love melodramatic movies too.</b>

145
00:16:00,660 --> 00:16:01,930
<b>So tell me.</b>

146
00:16:01,930 --> 00:16:03,230
<b>I went to Jun Seo's school...</b>

147
00:16:03,230 --> 00:16:05,270
<b>and found out her son was the other kid.</b>

148
00:16:05,500 --> 00:16:06,670
<b>His grades are superb,</b>

149
00:16:06,670 --> 00:16:07,930
<b>but his family's poor,</b>

150
00:16:07,930 --> 00:16:10,000
<b>so she's been working hard to support him.</b>

151
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,640
<b>I thought if something were to happen to the kid,</b>

152
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:12,970
<b>things would get worse for her.</b>

153
00:16:13,340 --> 00:16:16,340
<b>- That's it? - How about teaching Jun Seo morals?</b>

154
00:16:16,510 --> 00:16:18,650
<b>He's doing what he did in elementary school.</b>

155
00:16:18,710 --> 00:16:21,280
<b>Are you saying Jun Seo made him do what he did?</b>

156
00:16:21,550 --> 00:16:23,020
<b>It's quite likely.</b>

157
00:16:23,020 --> 00:16:25,020
<b>This is why I told you to...</b>

158
00:16:25,350 --> 00:16:28,020
<b>pay more attention to him.</b>

159
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:31,460
<b>I'm not the kind of person...</b>

160
00:16:31,460 --> 00:16:33,430
<b>who can teach or change someone.</b>

161
00:16:34,130 --> 00:16:35,660
<b>I will pay more attention.</b>

162
00:16:35,830 --> 00:16:38,330
<b>And if possible, I'll pick him up on Saturdays.</b>

163
00:16:39,530 --> 00:16:41,230
<b>You should've done that before.</b>

164
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,900
<b>But honey.</b>

165
00:16:46,370 --> 00:16:48,610
<b>Why won't you ask me about...</b>

166
00:16:48,810 --> 00:16:50,910
<b>my relations with the model?</b>

167
00:16:53,450 --> 00:16:54,710
<b>Do you not care?</b>

168
00:16:54,710 --> 00:16:57,020
<b>It's not something to applaud you for,</b>

169
00:16:57,650 --> 00:16:59,320
<b>but I feel partially responsible.</b>

170
00:16:59,650 --> 00:17:01,590
<b>I was in prison for four years...</b>

171
00:17:02,060 --> 00:17:03,860
<b>and was busy with work before then.</b>

172
00:17:03,860 --> 00:17:06,360
<b>Is that it? Aren't you even angry?</b>

173
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:12,370
<b>It looks like you want to say something.</b>

174
00:17:12,370 --> 00:17:13,570
<b>So I'll ask.</b>

175
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:16,370
<b>Why did you see another man?</b>

176
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:17,800
<b>When I happened to be...</b>

177
00:17:18,670 --> 00:17:20,340
<b>away in the dark?</b>

178
00:17:23,980 --> 00:17:25,710
<b>Because I was lonely.</b>

179
00:17:27,580 --> 00:17:30,520
<b>I don't have friends or siblings.</b>

180
00:17:31,320 --> 00:17:32,850
<b>All I have...</b>

181
00:17:33,250 --> 00:17:35,160
<b>is Dad and you.</b>

182
00:17:35,560 --> 00:17:37,860
<b>Neither of you were with me then.</b>

183
00:17:39,890 --> 00:17:41,390
<b>So...</b>

184
00:17:42,130 --> 00:17:43,960
<b>don't make me lonely.</b>

185
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:46,870
<b>I can't stand being lonely.</b>

186
00:17:48,670 --> 00:17:50,840
<b>Liking someone who doesn't like me back.</b>

187
00:17:51,640 --> 00:17:53,640
<b>I hate things like that.</b>

188
00:17:58,040 --> 00:18:00,810
<b>Mr. Han looks great in a suit,</b>

189
00:18:01,150 --> 00:18:04,280
<b>so even a basic design like this would work too.</b>

190
00:18:04,280 --> 00:18:06,450
<b>Everyone knows he looks good in a suit.</b>

191
00:18:06,620 --> 00:18:09,590
<b>But he has too many with the basic look.</b>

192
00:18:09,860 --> 00:18:13,230
<b>I want something with a unique texture or design.</b>

193
00:18:13,260 --> 00:18:16,800
<b>Okay. I'll ask our team leader when she arrives.</b>

194
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:22,370
<b>Did the gloves he bought you fit?</b>

195
00:18:24,040 --> 00:18:25,040
<b>What do you mean?</b>

196
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:27,110
<b>When Mr. Han was last here...</b>

197
00:18:27,110 --> 00:18:28,240
<b>Jin Young.</b>

198
00:18:30,210 --> 00:18:32,350
<b>What is she talking about?</b>

199
00:18:32,850 --> 00:18:34,980
<b>Did Jae Hyun buy something...</b>

200
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:36,380
<b>when he was here?</b>

201
00:18:37,650 --> 00:18:39,750
<b>Was it a woman's item?</b>

202
00:18:40,350 --> 00:18:41,990
<b>Well...</b>

203
00:18:43,590 --> 00:18:44,790
<b>Bring it to me.</b>

204
00:18:44,990 --> 00:18:47,890
<b>Let's see my husband's taste.</b>

205
00:18:53,630 --> 00:18:54,870
<b>She's a university friend.</b>

206
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:57,900
<b>Get up, Yoon Ji Su!</b>

207
00:19:10,350 --> 00:19:11,920
<b>Send in Secretary Kim.</b>

208
00:19:18,490 --> 00:19:19,730
<b>What's the matter?</b>

209
00:19:23,430 --> 00:19:24,500
<b>Number one.</b>

210
00:19:24,600 --> 00:19:26,830
<b>You found Ji Su but didn't tell me.</b>

211
00:19:26,830 --> 00:19:27,830
<b>Number two.</b>

212
00:19:28,130 --> 00:19:30,000
<b>You liked Ji Su. Which is it?</b>

213
00:19:30,170 --> 00:19:32,110
<b>Don't talk nonsense.</b>

214
00:19:32,340 --> 00:19:34,140
<b>You met the real Yoon Ji Su?</b>

215
00:19:35,980 --> 00:19:37,810
<b>Is she doing okay? No problems?</b>

216
00:19:38,080 --> 00:19:40,380
<b>Her son goes to the same school as my son.</b>

217
00:19:40,380 --> 00:19:43,780
<b>Wow, then she married into a rich family.</b>

218
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:46,790
<b>I was so anxious that...</b>

219
00:19:46,790 --> 00:19:48,260
<b>she'd end up...</b>

220
00:19:48,260 --> 00:19:51,190
<b>a divorcee who had left a violent husband.</b>

221
00:19:52,330 --> 00:19:54,960
<b>So, is she still pretty?</b>

222
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:57,460
<b>It was number two then.</b>

223
00:19:58,400 --> 00:19:59,400
<b>Number three.</b>

224
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:00,800
<b>What's that?</b>

225
00:20:00,870 --> 00:20:02,270
<b>I think that...</b>

226
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:05,140
<b>Ji Su had a huge crush on me.</b>

227
00:20:05,140 --> 00:20:06,440
<b>Didn't she mention me?</b>

228
00:20:08,740 --> 00:20:09,740
<b>No.</b>

229
00:20:18,820 --> 00:20:19,990
<b>Give me a moment.</b>

230
00:20:20,220 --> 00:20:22,290
<b>Take your time. You can't pee if you rush.</b>

231
00:22:11,920 --> 00:22:12,920
<b>Yes, ma'am.</b>

232
00:22:18,290 --> 00:22:19,890
<b>Yu Ri's not free today?</b>

233
00:22:20,590 --> 00:22:21,860
<b>That's too bad.</b>

234
00:22:23,660 --> 00:22:24,690
<b>It's okay.</b>

235
00:22:25,500 --> 00:22:26,630
<b>Thank you.</b>

236
